# 🧩 Chunk Streaming System

## Dynamic World Streaming Configuration

Maps support chunk-based world streaming.

Chunk data defines how large worlds are loaded and managed.

---

## Chunk Settings

| Property | Purpose |
|---|---|
| chunk_profile | Streaming configuration |
| chunk_size | World chunk dimensions |
| chunk_load_radius | Active chunk loading range |
| min_chunk_bounds | Minimum world boundary |
| max_chunk_bounds | Maximum world boundary |
| chunk_scene_template | Chunk scene source |
| chunk_data_template | Chunk data source |
| lod_distances | Level-of-detail distances |


---

# 🗺 Chunk Architecture

```

Map Resource

```
  |
  ▼
```

Chunk Manager

```
  |
  ├── Load Nearby Chunks
  ├── Unload Distant Chunks
  ├── Save Chunk State
  └── Apply LOD
```

```


The map resource defines the rules.

The chunk manager handles execution.


---

# 🎮 Gameplay Rules

Controls which gameplay systems are available within a map.

| Property | Purpose |
|---|---|
| allow_mounts | Enable mount usage |
| allow_fast_travel | Enable travel points |
| combat_enabled | Enable combat encounters |


Examples:

Safe Area:

```

combat_enabled = false
allow_fast_travel = true

```


Danger Zone:

```

combat_enabled = true
allow_fast_travel = false

```


---

# 💾 Persistence Rules

Controls what world objects survive saves.

| Property | Purpose |
|---|---|
| persistent_enemies | Save enemy states |
| persistent_loot | Save loot states |


Used by:

- Save Manager
- World State Manager
- Chunk Persistence System


Example:

```

Dungeon:
persistent_enemies = true
persistent_loot = true

```


---

# 🖥 Presentation Data

Controls how the map appears in UI systems.

| Property | Purpose |
|---|---|
| display_type | Map classification |
| minimap_enabled | Enable minimap rendering |
| debug_color | Editor/debug visualization |


Used by:

- Map UI
- World Map
- Debug tools


